# Elementor Widget Standards

## 1. Every Visible Color Must Be Editable

Use `Controls_Manager::COLOR` — never hardcode hex values in PHP or CSS that aren't driven by a control.

```php
$this->add_control( 'heading_color', [
    'label'     => esc_html__( 'Heading Color', 'trs-kit' ),
    'type'      => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::COLOR,
    'selectors' => [ '{{WRAPPER}} .trs-heading' => 'color: {{VALUE}};' ],
] );
```

## 2. Every Text Must Be Editable

Inline text/content → `Controls_Manager::TEXT` or `TEXTAREA`.  
Rich text → `Controls_Manager::WYSIWYG`.

```php
$this->add_control( 'heading_text', [
    'label'   => esc_html__( 'Heading', 'trs-kit' ),
    'type'    => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TEXT,
    'default' => esc_html__( 'Your Heading Here', 'trs-kit' ),
] );
```

## 3. Typography Controls

Every text element must have a paired `Group_Control_Typography`:

```php
$this->add_group_control(
    \Elementor\Group_Control_Typography::get_type(),
    [
        'name'     => 'heading_typography',
        'selector' => '{{WRAPPER}} .trs-heading',
    ]
);
```

## 4. Controls Organization

| Tab | Sections |
|-----|----------|
| **Content** | Content, Layout, Media |
| **Style** | Colors, Typography, Spacing, Border, Effects |
| **Advanced** | (Elementor native — do not add custom sections here) |

```php
$this->start_controls_section( 'section_content', [
    'label' => esc_html__( 'Content', 'trs-kit' ),
    'tab'   => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TAB_CONTENT,
] );
// ... controls ...
$this->end_controls_section();

$this->start_controls_section( 'section_style', [
    'label' => esc_html__( 'Style', 'trs-kit' ),
    'tab'   => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TAB_STYLE,
] );
```

## 5. Responsive Controls

Use `'responsive' => true` on Dimensions/Slider controls for automatic desktop/tablet/mobile breakpoints:

```php
$this->add_responsive_control( 'padding', [
    'label'      => esc_html__( 'Padding', 'trs-kit' ),
    'type'       => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::DIMENSIONS,
    'size_units' => [ 'px', 'em', '%' ],
    'selectors'  => [ '{{WRAPPER}} .trs-module' => 'padding: {{TOP}}{{UNIT}} {{RIGHT}}{{UNIT}} {{BOTTOM}}{{UNIT}} {{LEFT}}{{UNIT}};' ],
] );
```

## 6. CSS Architecture

- **All selectors must start with `{{WRAPPER}}`** — never use bare class names that would bleed across page.
- Write CSS mobile-first in the `.css` file; use Elementor breakpoints (`1025px` desktop, `768px` tablet, `767px` mobile) for overrides.
- Use CSS custom properties for values shared between elements inside the same widget:

```css
/* module-name.css */
.trs-module-name {
    --trs-primary-color: #000;
    --trs-gap: 1.5rem;
}

@media (max-width: 767px) {
    .trs-module-name { --trs-gap: 1rem; }
}
```

## 7. Render Method Rules

- Always escape output: `esc_html()`, `esc_url()`, `esc_attr()`, `wp_kses_post()`.
- Read controls via `$this->get_settings_for_display()`.
- Guard empty values before rendering markup.

```php
protected function render(): void {
    $settings = $this->get_settings_for_display();
    if ( empty( $settings['heading_text'] ) ) return;
    echo '<h2 class="trs-heading">' . esc_html( $settings['heading_text'] ) . '</h2>';
}
```

## 8. JavaScript

- Wrap in an IIFE; use `elementorFrontend.hooks` to initialise on editor reload:

```js
( function( $ ) {
    const initModule = ( $scope ) => {
        // init logic
    };

    $( window ).on( 'elementor/frontend/init', () => {
        elementorFrontend.hooks.addAction( 'frontend/element_ready/trs-module-name.default', initModule );
    } );
} )( jQuery );
```
